m to write the elegy:\n{{quote |''It is difficult to express in words exactly how I felt at losing so many of my friends, other than to say I was wracked with grief. As a composer, this build\u2013up of emotion had to go somewhere and it is my wish that in writing the elegy, I have managed to capture some of this strength of feeling.''<ref>{{cite report |editor-first1=Amanda|editor-last1=Bok|date=April 2013 |title=EHC Newsletter |url=https://www.yumpu.com/en/document/view/28554873/april-2013-ehc |publisher=European Haemophilia Consortium (EHC) |location=Brussels|page=27|access-date=2020-04-20|quote=Andrew March: ''Elegy dedicated to victims of contaminated blood''}}</ref>}}\n\n==Recording==\nThe piece was recorded in Reduta Hall, [[Olomouc]], [[Czech Republic]] on 9th July, 2011, by 50 string players from the [[Moravian Philharmonic]] under conductor, [[Petr Vronsk\u00fd]]. ''Sanguis Venenatus'' was released as the fourth track on the CD album ''Dimensions \u2013 Works for String Orchestra'' by Navona Records (NV5895) on 13 November 2012.<ref>{{cite book | title=Dimensions \u2013 Works for String Orchestra| oclc=1114084658}}</ref> The ''Dimensions'' album was reviewed in Gramophone in March 2013, where [[Donald Rosenberg]] said that ''Sanguis Venenatus'' was \u2033intensly felt\u2033 and that the elegy was characterised by \u2033slow, aching lines and mild dissonances\".<ref name=\"Gramophone1\" />\n\n==Performances==\nThe world premi\u00e8re of ''Sanguis Venenatus'' was given on Saturday 20th March, 2010, at [[Todmorden]] Town Hall, by the strings of the Todmorden Orchestra under conductor Nicholas Concannon Hodges. The premi\u00e8re was followed by positive review describing the one\u2013movement elegy as a first\u2013hand musical metaphor for thousands of haemophiliacs given contaminated blood.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.todmordenorchestra.org.uk/reviews/ |title=Reviews: March 20th 2010, Todmorden Town Hall |last=Issac |first=Stuart |date=20 March 2010 |website=www.todmordenorchestra.org.uk |publisher=Todmorden Orchestra |access-date=2020-04-22 |quote=}}</ref> On Wednesday 30th March, 2011, the elegy received a second performance during a commemorative service at Westminster Abbey with the strings of the London Charity Orchestra under William Carslake. The service celebrated the 40th anniversary of the enactment of the Chronically Sick and Disabled Persons Act (1970).<ref name=\"Westminster1\" /><ref name=\"Navona1\" />\n\n==Broadcasts==\nThe first known radio broadcast of ''Sanguis Venenatus'' was on [[WPRB|WPRB 103.3]] fm [[Princeton, New Jersey]], on 28th November 2012.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://andrewmarch.com/59274/97146.html |title= News updates for Sanguis Venenatus|date=2012-08-28 |access-date=2020-04-24 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180823023841/http://andrewmarch.com/59274/97146.html |archive-date=2012-08-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.classicaldiscoveries.org/playlist20121128c_g.html|title= Classical Discoveries|author=<!--Not stated--> |date=28 November 2012 |website= WPRB 103.3 FM|publisher= |access-date=2020-04-24 |quote= ''Sanguis Venenatus'' (Tainted Blood)}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Contaminated blood scandal in the United Kingdom]]\n*[[Marine \u2013 \u00e0 travers les arbres]] (winning piece of the first Masterprize)\n*[[R (March) v Secretary of State for Health]] (judicial review involving victims of contaminated blood products)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=W4gy-7IlUqg YouTube, (''Sanguis Venenatus'')]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1hJ4O21moxc YouTube (Deezer), (''Sanguis Venenatus'' Moravian Philharmonic Orchestra)]\n* [http://radiofy.se/artists/828892-andrew-march/songs/1-sanguis-venenatus Radiofy, ''Sanguis Venenatus'' av Andrew March] {{In lang|sv}}\n* [http://www.pandora.com/artist/moravian-philharmonic-orchestra/dimensions-works-for-string-orchestra/sanguis-venenatus-for-orchestra/TRdV7X5gcgx2bxJ Pandora (Streaming) ''Sanguis Venenatus'' (Dimensions)]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Works about contaminated haemophilia blood products]]\n[[Category:Music with dedications]]\n[[Category:Compositions for string orchestra]]\n[[Category:Funerary and memorial compositions]]\n[[Category:2009 compositions]]\n\n{{Music-stub}}\n", "name_user": "SpookiePuppy", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eSee also:Adding italics to composition title.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sanguis_Venenatus"}
